## Limitations
This report is limited by the availability of current data and the scope of perspectives included. The sources primarily reflect pro-taxation viewpoints, and there may be other economic theories and empirical data that offer counterarguments. Additionally, the complexity of tax policy and its varied impacts across different economies are not fully explored in this brief report. Further research could provide a more comprehensive understanding of the implications of taxing the rich more heavily.

